topic.title: GFP-F Mapping and Interlaken Throughput Considerations for Packet Traffic

body.p: Packets transferred from the Interlaken or Ethernet interfaces can be GFP-F mapped directly into an OPUk. The system throughput is a function of the number of bytes transferred over Interlaken, the throughput limit of the device Interlaken processor, the bandwidth expansion as a result of bytes that are added to form the GFP frame, and the capacity of the OPUk.
